WEBVTT

00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:05.920
In this short video, we'll go through the process of deploying a Shiny for Python application

00:00:06.480 --> 00:00:13.920
from Posit Workbench, here I am in VS Code, to Posit Connect. So just to give you a lay of the

00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:19.280
land, so what you're seeing right here is a Shiny for Python application called app.py,

00:00:19.280 --> 00:00:22.879
and that resides in a directory I've created called Shiny for Python.

00:00:23.760 --> 00:00:28.719
So to get started, let's go ahead and install some packages we'll need for this workflow.

00:00:28.719 --> 00:00:36.880
So I'm going to use pip to install the Shiny package. Also rsconnect Python, which is used

00:00:36.880 --> 00:00:43.360
to deploy applications to connect. And then you can see this application depends on two popular

00:00:43.919 --> 00:00:48.560
data science packages, matplotlib and numpy. So let's make sure we install those as well.

00:00:52.560 --> 00:00:56.480
I believe I already have these in my environment. So it should say requirement already satisfied.

00:00:56.480 --> 00:01:02.080
So that's great, we are in a good spot. Now before we deploy to Posit Connect, let's just

00:01:02.080 --> 00:01:08.239
make sure this application runs correctly locally here within VS Code running on Posit Workbench.

00:01:08.879 --> 00:01:14.639
So I'll run shiny run and the name of the file app.py, hit enter.

00:01:18.320 --> 00:01:24.639
And we'll get a URL that I can then click on. And here is our Shiny for Python application.

00:01:24.639 --> 00:01:30.160
It's a simple slider bar that changes the number of bins in the histogram as I move it left and

00:01:30.160 --> 00:01:37.360
right. Alright, so it appears to be working well. And then the last thing we'll do is go ahead and

00:01:37.360 --> 00:01:44.639
deploy it to Posit Connect. And we'll use the rsconnect package to help with this. So rsconnect

00:01:44.639 --> 00:01:51.120
deploy shiny, you have to give it the name of the connect server you want to deploy to. So I'll use

00:01:51.120 --> 00:01:58.320
the dash n argument. And I have the server saved my environment as PCT prod. And then just give it

00:01:58.320 --> 00:02:03.760
the name of the directory that houses the app.py file. I'm currently within this directory. So I'll

00:02:03.760 --> 00:02:12.960
just use the period as a shorthand and hit enter. It'll run through a few checks, make sure my

00:02:12.960 --> 00:02:18.000
environment is being captured and recorded and sent to connect to replicate that environment.

00:02:18.880 --> 00:02:25.199
And once that is done, it'll deploy to Posit Connect and we'll get two URLs here at the bottom,

00:02:25.199 --> 00:02:30.080
I can click on this bottom one and it will actually bring me straight to Posit Connect.

00:02:30.080 --> 00:02:35.440
And here we have that same application running on the connect instance. And that is how you can

00:02:35.440 --> 00:02:39.919
deploy a shiny for Python application to Posit Connect.

